 that appeared unto thee when thou fleddest from the face of Esau thy brother."},{"id":"recOcRA9mKNQqqHNQ","ref":"Gen.35.2","text":"Then Jacob said unto his household, and to all that were with him, Put away the strange gods that are among you, and be clean, and change your garments:"},{"id":"rec0icRJj4vO10BfB","ref":"Gen.35.3","text":"And let us arise, and go up to Bethel; and I will make there an altar unto God, who answered me in the day of my distress, and was with me in the way which I went."},{"id":"recZeBUSFYehiFvZv","ref":"Gen.35.4","text":"And they gave unto Jacob all the strange gods which were in their hand, and all their earrings which were in their ears; and Jacob hid them under the oak which was by Shechem."},{"id":"recI3OOZuZ1neMY6R","ref":"Gen.35.5","text":"And they journeyed: and the terror of God was upon the cities that were round about them, and they did not pursue after the sons of Jacob."},{"id":"rec7IWn4X4hzfQtFK","ref":"Gen.35.6","text":"So Jacob came to Luz, which is in the land of Canaan, that is, Bethel, he and all the people that were with him."},{"id":"recWHPe0BcGRE4Ln1","ref":"Gen.35.7","text":"And he built there an altar, and called the place Elbethel: because there God appeared unto him, when he fled from the face of his brother."},{"id":"recqk0AFbvHsOrsbc","ref":"Gen.35.8","text":"But Deborah Rebekah’s nurse died, and she was buried beneath Bethel under an oak: and the name of it was called Allonbachuth."}]}
